1
00:00:29,880 --> 00:00:32,250
<i>Why isn't anyone helping me get up?</i>

2
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:34,510
<i>Why?</i>

3
00:00:40,900 --> 00:00:42,770
<i>Let's just end this here.</i>

4
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:44,630
<i>This is too hard.</i>

5
00:00:45,650 --> 00:00:47,350
<i>It's just too hard.</i>

6
00:00:50,630 --> 00:00:51,899
<i>No.</i>

7
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:53,520
<i>I have to live.</i>

8
00:00:54,210 --> 00:00:55,679
<i>I want to live.</i>

9
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,139
<i>Someone...</i>

10
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,779
<i>Someone grab me.</i>

11
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:02,780
<i>I want someone to grab me!</i>

12
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:43,020
How much do you think
this building costs?

13
00:01:43,730 --> 00:01:44,970
Excuse me?

14
00:01:45,540 --> 00:01:47,720
Do you think that there's
anyone out there

15
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:49,930
who'd want to exchange
their life for this?

16
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,739
By any chance...

17
00:01:58,740 --> 00:02:00,730
Do you know of any
restrooms in the area

18
00:02:00,740 --> 00:02:02,740
where a lot of homeless
people frequents?

19
00:02:19,670 --> 00:02:20,900
What?

20
00:02:21,810 --> 00:02:25,749
I'm sorry, but the patients in this
area needs absolute peace and quiet.

21
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:27,709
You cannot interview
anyone in this area.

22
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:28,960
Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk is
admitted here, isn't he?

23
00:02:28,970 --> 00:02:30,230
Yes, he is.

24
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,230
Then I guess we can't do
anything else about it.

25
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,900
I'm sure he'll have
to come out sometime.

26
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:36,110
Let's just wait for him.

27
00:02:44,670 --> 00:02:47,000
- Yes, Director.
- How's his condition now?

28
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,210
Okay.

29
00:02:49,220 --> 00:02:51,460
Don't let him out of your sight
until I get there.

30
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:53,279
Okay.

31
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,249
Add him to the family registry quickly.

32
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:56,860
But all the reporters
are there already.

33
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:58,500
Reporters?

34
00:03:00,490 --> 00:03:02,080
There's Kang Ji Hyuk right there.

35
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:05,359
Is it true that you're
Chairman Kang Sung Wook's hidden son?

36
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,139
What's the reason for keeping
that truth a secret all this time?

37
00:03:07,140 --> 00:03:09,969
How do you think things will change as
you come on board as a new heir?

38
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:12,529
When did you find out that you're
Chairman Kang Sung Wook's son?

39
00:03:12,530 --> 00:03:14,420
Is that fact related to
your recent accident?

40
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:17,000
What are you guys talking about?

41
00:03:17,010 --> 00:03:19,350
- Aren't you Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk?
- Kang Ji Hyuk?

42
00:03:20,230 --> 00:03:22,260
My name is Kim Ji Hyuk.

43
00:03:24,290 --> 00:03:25,700
<i>Ji Hyuk.</i>

44
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:33,800
Ji Hyuk.

45
00:03:40,610 --> 00:03:42,690
What a relief to see that you're okay.

46
00:03:44,110 --> 00:03:46,030
I'm so glad to see you, Ji Hyuk.

47
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:05,940
Do you remember anything
from your childhood?

48
00:04:07,690 --> 00:04:09,200
No.

49
00:04:09,820 --> 00:04:11,360
I don't remember a thing.

50
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:21,219
Let's not rush anything.

51
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:24,739
Once we come to terms with our own
emotions, and get used to each other

52
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:29,100
I'm sure we'll be able to form a bond
as father and son, and as family then.

53
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:32,540
You understand what I'm
saying, don't you?

54
00:04:34,890 --> 00:04:36,770
No, I have no idea what you're saying.

55
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:39,849
Okay, I understand.

56
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:42,770
I'm sure you must be flustered since
that's the way I'm feeling right now.

57
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:46,630
What I'm saying is that we both should
take some time to get used to the idea.

58
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:51,030
Get some rest for now.

59
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,770
What do you do for a living?

60
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:02,130
You'll find that out soon enough.

61
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:05,189
Do I have a mother?

62
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:07,079
Of course you do.

63
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,540
Really?

64
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:14,260
- Does she know?
- Of course.

65
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:23,720
You should've just let
the sleeping dogs lie.

66
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:26,430
We're just going to complicate
everything for one another.

67
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:28,490
I can't do that.

68
00:05:29,180 --> 00:05:31,360
Because you're my son.

69
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,800
Because I'm your son?

70
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:48,250
What's the point of seeking me out now?

71
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:07,439
Why are they getting so curious about
our family registry all of a sudden?

72
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:09,600
I think they received a request
from the investigators.

73
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:11,190
I think they must've
discovered something

74
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,589
that may have been
done illegally.

75
00:06:12,590 --> 00:06:15,639
Ugh, why now of all times?

76
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,680
Forget it. I don't
think we need to worry

77
00:06:17,690 --> 00:06:19,740
about it since the
office will soon change.

78
00:06:20,410 --> 00:06:22,379
Did you look into the foreign matters
that I told you to look into?

79
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:24,329
Yes, I think we'll get an
answer from them soon.

80
00:06:24,330 --> 00:06:25,609
You think it'll work?

81
00:06:25,610 --> 00:06:27,409
I think there's more than
a 90 percent chance that it will.

82
00:06:27,410 --> 00:06:28,610
Is that right?

83
00:06:32,050 --> 00:06:33,699
And one more thing.

84
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,759
That guy...

85
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:39,679
I want you to confuse him. Throw money,
women, and whatever else at him.

86
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,999
So that he doesn't have a chance
to think about anything else.

87
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,130
Yes, Sir.

88
00:06:45,830 --> 00:06:47,790
That's the life history
of Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk

89
00:06:47,810 --> 00:06:49,780
that we have of
him up to this point.

90
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:53,640
Don't you rather that you didn't know
any of that?

91
00:06:54,570 --> 00:06:58,259
- Why do I have to know any of this?
- Because he's part of the family.

92
00:06:58,260 --> 00:07:00,340
He's someone whom you need to serve.

93
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,059
I started searching for Kang Ji Hyuk's

94
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:07,230
whereabouts about a year ago
per Chairman Kang's orders.

95
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:10,149
I found out about Kang Ji
Hyuk's existence very recently

96
00:07:10,150 --> 00:07:11,990
and I was able to find
his DNA records purely

97
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,850
by coincidence from
his recent accident.

98
00:07:14,690 --> 00:07:16,380
That's the result of all my findings.

99
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:29,759
I just prepared some things that
I thought you may need for the moment.

100
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:32,229
Just let me know if there's
anything else that you need.

101
00:07:32,230 --> 00:07:33,980
And one more thing.

102
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:37,920
This is the key to the car
that you'll be driving.

103
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,910
Let me know if the car
isn't to your liking

104
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:41,490
and I'll swap it out
for something else.

105
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:48,590
Are you trying to recruit me right now?

106
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:52,259
You know how those sports teams always
gets the players whatever they want

107
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:53,669
when trying to recruit them?

108
00:07:53,670 --> 00:07:57,360
Getting them an amazing place to live
with a fancy car to boot.

109
00:07:57,770 --> 00:08:00,800
There's no one in this world
who tries to recruit a son.

110
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:06,280
I'm sure you guys can do all this
since that guy has so much money.

111
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:10,569
Anyways, this is nice.

112
00:08:10,570 --> 00:08:12,110
Getting a chance to live...

113
00:08:13,220 --> 00:08:16,170
in an amazing place like this
for having met a nice set of parents.

114
00:08:22,410 --> 00:08:24,230
Money sure is nice.

115
00:08:31,620 --> 00:08:34,770
<i>I want you to bring that scoundrel
back here and rip his heart out!</i>

116
00:08:37,670 --> 00:08:39,640
What floor are we even on?

117
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:08,110
Crap!

118
00:09:13,950 --> 00:09:15,440
Thank you.

119
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:19,440
For some strange reason,
I keep having to receive help from you.

120
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,040
Um...

121
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:27,000
Call me anytime if there's
anything else that you need.

122
00:09:28,220 --> 00:09:29,700
Yeah, sure.

123
00:09:30,490 --> 00:09:31,890
But...

124
00:09:33,420 --> 00:09:35,460
What is it that you do for them?

125
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:41,530
I'm an employee of Hyun Sung Group.

126
00:09:42,010 --> 00:09:44,160
I take care of
Chairman Kang's family.

127
00:09:44,170 --> 00:09:46,346
Really?

128
00:09:46,370 --> 00:09:49,096
Then I guess you must get to see
those parents of mine pretty often?

129
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:51,770
- Yes, I do.
- Go give them a message for me.

130
00:09:53,310 --> 00:09:55,800
Tell them that I'm
tearfully grateful for

131
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:58,320
buying me this grand
house and the fancy car.

132
00:10:00,380 --> 00:10:04,049
The son that they just threw away
and abandoned for the past 30 years...

133
00:10:04,050 --> 00:10:06,849
is speechless with utter gratefulness.

134
00:10:06,850 --> 00:10:08,590
Please make sure to
relay that message.

135
00:10:09,790 --> 00:10:11,160
Yes, Sir.

136
00:10:18,340 --> 00:10:20,100
Now it's raining?

137
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:23,690
Well that's just depressing.

138
00:10:44,820 --> 00:10:47,700
You told me to let you know if there's
anything else I might need, right?

139
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:51,109
Yes, tell me.

140
00:10:51,110 --> 00:10:52,799
What is it that you need?

141
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:55,340
An extra umbrella so
that I may be able to

142
00:10:55,350 --> 00:10:57,900
shield a lady from getting
soaked in the rain.

143
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:24,970
Dong Suk.

144
00:11:26,330 --> 00:11:29,480
You're going to get up from that bed
as if nothing even happened, right?

145
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:33,449
I've been so afraid...

146
00:11:33,450 --> 00:11:36,060
and because of that...

147
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:39,540
I've never even once got to
tell you that I love you.

148
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:46,490
So please just get up from that bed.

149
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,530
I can't live without you.

150
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:02,160
Oh my, look who it is!
Ji Hyuk's here.

151
00:12:02,170 --> 00:12:03,439
Yes, it's me.

152
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,940
- Are you well?
- Of course!

153
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,829
Why are you still following me?

154
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:12,810
It's my job to do so.

155
00:12:17,090 --> 00:12:18,530
Mom!

156
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,619
- Mom!
- What are you doing!

157
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:23,220
Get away from me!
You're grossing me out!

158
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:26,289
Mom, do you have any idea
how much I've missed you?

159
00:12:26,290 --> 00:12:28,509
- You must've been so worried about me.
- Don't' talk crazy.

160
00:12:28,510 --> 00:12:31,589
Why would I worry about you?
I'm busy enough as is with my own life.

161
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:33,949
Excuse me, but are you his mother?

162
00:12:33,950 --> 00:12:36,899
His mother?
Mother, my butt.

163
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:39,339
He thinks that all the middle aged
women in this world are his mom.

164
00:12:39,340 --> 00:12:41,429
Especially if there's something
that he can gain from the woman.

165
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:42,740
I bet he probably has
more than 30 women

166
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:44,069
in this market alone
whom he calls 'mom'.

167
00:12:44,070 --> 00:12:46,299
No, Mom.
They're just regular moms.

168
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:48,260
But you're my mom.

169
00:12:48,710 --> 00:12:51,680
Stop kissing my face.
Hey!

170
00:12:52,350 --> 00:12:54,709
Where and what have you been
doing these past few days?

171
00:12:54,710 --> 00:12:57,290
And... who is this young lady?

172
00:12:57,930 --> 00:12:59,829
Did you cause another accident?

173
00:12:59,830 --> 00:13:01,330
Accident?

174
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:04,159
Yeah, I did.
A huge accident.

175
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,620
You didn't.

176
00:13:07,290 --> 00:13:09,779
- Before you're even married?
- Excuse me?

177
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:12,539
Come on, Mom!
What do you take me for?

178
00:13:12,540 --> 00:13:14,889
You're painting a bad picture of me
in front of this lady.

179
00:13:14,890 --> 00:13:19,260
Don't let her mislead you.
I'm much more virtuous than I may look.

180
00:13:20,460 --> 00:13:22,950
Mrs. Hong!
Mrs. Hong, Ji Hyuk is...

181
00:13:23,550 --> 00:13:25,499
Ji... Ji Hyuk!

182
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,289
Your Highness!

183
00:13:27,290 --> 00:13:29,320
Please forgive me for
not having recognized

184
00:13:29,340 --> 00:13:31,380
your status to have
served you properly.

185
00:13:31,930 --> 00:13:35,740
I swear to pledge the rest of my life
in your servitude, Your Highness!

186
00:13:36,270 --> 00:13:37,969
What's wrong with you now?

187
00:13:37,970 --> 00:13:40,420
I told you that I caused
a slight accident.

188
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,439
- What is he talking about?
- Ji Hyuk is...

189
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,530
You know the company,
Hyun Sung Group, right?

190
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:45,639
Yeah.

191
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:50,710
He's that Chairman's son! It's all
over the internet and the newspapers!

192
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:57,250
- Is he serious?
- It's not a sure thing yet.

193
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:00,740
But that's what those
people are saying.

194
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:02,910
There's something that
I have to show you.

195
00:14:08,990 --> 00:14:12,430
Is what I heard on the news... true?

196
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,680
What is it?

197
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:18,370
Is he mom's son too?

198
00:14:18,380 --> 00:14:21,410
- Or is he just your son, Dad?
- Your mom gave birth to him.

199
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:24,280
Honey.

200
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:28,710
Madame Choi, he came from your womb.
You can't even remember that?

201
00:14:31,410 --> 00:14:33,120
This is crazy.

202
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:35,900
Thanks, Dad.

203
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,140
You kept this a secret
for how many decades

204
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:39,829
just so that you could
surprise me like this?

205
00:14:39,830 --> 00:14:43,729
I sincerely thank you. It was the
biggest surprise gift of my life.

206
00:14:43,730 --> 00:14:45,670
Surprise!

207
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:50,820
What was the point of
lying to Jin Ah too?

208
00:14:50,830 --> 00:14:53,010
Then you go tell her the truth.

209
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,119
Tell her that we smacked a perfectly
healthy guy on his head

210
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,340
and lied about him
being our son just so

211
00:14:57,350 --> 00:14:58,630
we could save
our own son's life.

212
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:01,450
Tell her that's how
evil her parents are.

213
00:15:02,630 --> 00:15:04,140
Go tell her that.

214
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,009
Wow, this is like a scene
right out of a movie.

215
00:15:07,010 --> 00:15:08,930
I feel like we're in a drama.
So they've

216
00:15:08,940 --> 00:15:10,869
been watching you all this time?

217
00:15:10,870 --> 00:15:14,549
Couldn't a document like this have
been forged if you guys had wanted to?

218
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:16,329
It's not like they were shot
in the head or something.

219
00:15:16,330 --> 00:15:18,109
Why would they want to
claim you as their son?

220
00:15:18,110 --> 00:15:20,050
What use could you be
to them when you've

221
00:15:20,060 --> 00:15:22,000
got nothing to offer
them but your body?

222
00:15:23,180 --> 00:15:24,409
Don't you agree?

223
00:15:24,410 --> 00:15:27,650
If you have a hard time believing me,
I can get it authenticated for you.

224
00:15:32,110 --> 00:15:35,820
Well... there's no need to go through
all that trouble.

225
00:15:35,830 --> 00:15:37,110
Hey.

226
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:40,639
I think others are right about that.
You're being suspicious over nothing.

227
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:43,990
You should just be grateful that
they even sought out a son like you.

228
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:56,270
<i>I told you that I'm too
busy to come tomorrow.</i>

229
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,290
<i>What?</i>

230
00:15:59,230 --> 00:16:02,380
Why do you have to put it like that?

231
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:07,030
Forget it.
I don't need your chump change.

232
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:08,850
You're the one who needs
to get it straight.

233
00:16:08,860 --> 00:16:09,940
I'm hanging up.

234
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:15,170
- How unbelievable.
- Who was that?

235
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:17,400
That was Mr. Kim.

236
00:16:18,420 --> 00:16:19,760
Mr. Kim from the butcher
shop at the market?

237
00:16:19,780 --> 00:16:21,119
Yeah.

238
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:23,619
When I told him that I was going
to take the day off tomorrow

239
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:25,909
he threatened that he wasn't going
to pay me my wages that he owes me.

240
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:28,620
It's not like it's a lot of money.
It's just 100,000 won.

241
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:34,170
Maybe we should just
buy his butcher shop.

242
00:16:34,180 --> 00:16:36,960
I bet 20-30 million won
is all we would need.

243
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:42,780
Ji Hyuk, since we're just
sitting around here,

244
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:45,060
should we call up those
girls for a date?

245
00:16:45,430 --> 00:16:47,550
Don't you think that
they'd go out on a date

246
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,680
with us if we got them
a commercial deal?

247
