00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:42,850
Look here, Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk.

498
00:35:43,250 --> 00:35:46,520
Let me give you a piece of advice.

499
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:50,549
But don't get your pride all ruffled up
where it's not needed.

500
00:35:50,550 --> 00:35:53,070
Take the money and
spend it all you like,

501
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:55,610
and do everything you've
ever wanted to do.

502
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:58,140
Buy everything you've
ever wanted to buy, and

503
00:35:58,160 --> 00:36:00,270
eat everything you've
ever wanted to eat.

504
00:36:00,780 --> 00:36:02,559
That's what you should do.

505
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:04,469
Why aren't you doing any of that?

506
00:36:04,470 --> 00:36:05,660
Why?

507
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:08,149
Why aren't you spending any money
when they're telling you to?

508
00:36:08,150 --> 00:36:09,450
Spend as much as you'd like!

509
00:36:09,780 --> 00:36:11,310
I've never once...

510
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:13,949
thought of their money as mine.

511
00:36:13,950 --> 00:36:18,250
That's why... that's why you're a fool.

512
00:36:19,100 --> 00:36:21,100
- A fool.
- Excuse me?

513
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:42,880
Thank you for still being alive.

514
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:52,630
This is a nice neighborhood.

515
00:37:17,620 --> 00:37:19,850
Can you come over here and
help me pick one out?

516
00:37:28,230 --> 00:37:32,090
I've never been overseas before,
so I'm not sure which one to get.

517
00:37:36,230 --> 00:37:39,410
Um... why didn't you ever join
a girl group or something?

518
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:41,330
Excuse me?

519
00:37:41,340 --> 00:37:42,900
I don't think it's
too late for you yet.

520
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:46,590
You should start training or something.
You're a pretty good singer.

521
00:37:48,240 --> 00:37:50,199
What are you talking about?

522
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:53,140
- You don't remember last night?
- No, not at all.

523
00:37:53,390 --> 00:37:55,090
You must've been really
drunk last night.

524
00:37:55,100 --> 00:37:56,819
I understand.

525
00:37:56,820 --> 00:38:01,150
Because I myself confuse my dreams from
reality from time to time when I drink.

526
00:38:03,010 --> 00:38:04,640
What do you think about this one?

527
00:38:09,380 --> 00:38:12,170
Let me know if you need anything else.

528
00:38:12,180 --> 00:38:14,200
No, I'm all set with this.

529
00:38:18,680 --> 00:38:21,209
I forgot you told me to
go spend all my money.

530
00:38:21,210 --> 00:38:23,859
I should just blow all my money here.

531
00:38:23,860 --> 00:38:27,489
You called me a fool and
told me to spend all my money.

532
00:38:27,490 --> 00:38:31,340
Let's go. I'm going to blow
some serious money on you today.

533
00:38:31,350 --> 00:38:34,249
No. I didn't tell you to
spend it on someone else.

534
00:38:34,250 --> 00:38:36,220
I told you to spend it on yourself...

535
00:38:37,750 --> 00:38:38,990
So you do remember.

536
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,480
You should've told me
that you remember!

537
00:38:41,500 --> 00:38:42,999
Why are you trying to lie to me?

538
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:44,570
Let's go. I'll show
you how I can spend...

539
00:38:44,590 --> 00:38:46,169
No, please don't be like this.

540
00:38:46,170 --> 00:38:48,940
Everyone can make a mistake or two
when they're drunk. Let's go.

541
00:38:48,950 --> 00:38:50,520
I told you to stop doing this!

542
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:56,680
- I was just...
- I'm sorry, but I'm working right now.

543
00:38:57,430 --> 00:38:59,050
I hope that we don't make
things uncomfortable

544
00:38:59,060 --> 00:39:00,690
for each other
while I'm working.

545
00:39:01,970 --> 00:39:04,170
<i>Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk?</i>

546
00:39:05,390 --> 00:39:07,219
I'm Reporter Bae from WVS News.

547
00:39:07,220 --> 00:39:09,560
I met you at the hospital.
Can you give me an interview?

548
00:39:09,570 --> 00:39:10,850
- What do you think?
- Huh?

549
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:14,120
- What interview?
- I'm sorry, but we must get going.

550
00:39:14,130 --> 00:39:15,509
- I just need a few minutes.
- No, I'm sorry.

551
00:39:15,510 --> 00:39:18,150
Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk!
Wait!

552
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:20,880
What did you and the
Chairman talk about?

553
00:39:20,890 --> 00:39:22,050
I told you that you
can't interview him.

554
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:23,239
What did you two talk about?

555
00:39:23,240 --> 00:39:24,770
Where does your shares
stand compared to.

556
00:39:24,780 --> 00:39:26,319
Director Kang Dong
Suk at the company?

557
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:28,550
I told you that you
can't interview him!

558
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:30,380
Reporter Bae!

559
00:39:34,050 --> 00:39:39,940
Don't you think that it's time for you
to make a move in your career?

560
00:39:41,780 --> 00:39:44,489
If a man like you came to
work for me at my company

561
00:39:44,490 --> 00:39:46,420
I have a feeling that we could be
quite successful together.

562
00:39:46,430 --> 00:39:47,790
Sir.

563
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:49,830
Why don't you just be frank with me?

564
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:52,419
What is it that you
want to hear from me?

565
00:39:52,420 --> 00:39:55,139
I'll just be honest with you
since you're my junior.

566
00:39:55,140 --> 00:39:57,700
Why do you keep digging
around my company?

567
00:40:00,810 --> 00:40:02,419
You know a man by the name
of Jung Won Tae, don't' you?

568
00:40:02,420 --> 00:40:04,646
He was the prosecutor for
Seoul's eastern district?

569
00:40:04,670 --> 00:40:07,559
- Yes, I know him.
- You owe him a debt, don't you?

570
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:09,289
When he got transferred down to Busan?

571
00:40:09,290 --> 00:40:12,479
Are you saying that I'm responsible
for his transfer?

572
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:17,149
It has been decided that he'll be
promoted to Chief Prosecutor.

573
00:40:17,150 --> 00:40:19,009
Even though he's slightly starting to
dig around right now

574
00:40:19,010 --> 00:40:21,799
he's going to get serious about it
once he's officially promoted.

575
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:25,270
I think it would be wise for you to
prepare yourself for a serious battle.

576
00:40:54,290 --> 00:40:55,689
Ta da!

577
00:40:55,690 --> 00:40:57,389
- Study hard, okay?
- Okay!

578
00:40:57,390 --> 00:40:59,599
Okay, next!

579
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:01,989
- Thank you!
- You're so cute! How old are you?

580
00:41:01,990 --> 00:41:03,830
- I'm five years old.
- You're five?

581
00:41:06,090 --> 00:41:08,150
Study hard, okay?

582
00:41:12,860 --> 00:41:14,430
I want something else.

583
00:41:15,180 --> 00:41:18,799
- Just take what you're given.
- I want a robot too!

584
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:21,519
I don't have another robot.
Just take the pink pencil case.

585
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:23,859
I want a robot!

586
00:41:23,860 --> 00:41:25,189
You little rascal.

587
00:41:25,190 --> 00:41:26,739
Give it back if you don't want it,
and I'll give it to someone else.

588
00:41:26,740 --> 00:41:27,880
Next.

589
00:41:30,390 --> 00:41:32,620
What?
Did you just kick me?

590
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:37,119
Would you look at this kid. How dare
you glare at an adult like that?

591
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:38,450
Come over here, you rascal.

592
00:41:39,780 --> 00:41:41,430
Hey!
Get over here right now!

593
00:41:45,390 --> 00:41:47,759
You've met your match today.
Come here!

594
00:41:47,760 --> 00:41:49,150
Come over here right now!

595
00:41:51,980 --> 00:41:54,300
How dare you act like I used to
when I was a kid?

596
00:41:54,810 --> 00:41:56,210
I'm going to drown
you with my kisses!

597
00:41:56,220 --> 00:41:57,640
Let go of me!

598
00:42:01,820 --> 00:42:03,460
My Sister Mom!

599
00:42:03,860 --> 00:42:06,660
This is not a lie, but I'm really
going to come here often from now on.

600
00:42:07,020 --> 00:42:11,220
No, it's okay. Don't worry about me,
and you just go live a happy life.

601
00:42:11,610 --> 00:42:14,519
Okay, always be healthy,
and I'm going to get going now.

602
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:16,320
No need to see me out.
I'm going to get going.

603
00:42:16,630 --> 00:42:17,950
Ji Hyuk, wait.

604
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:20,629
I've been holding onto something
that may have helped you

605
00:42:20,630 --> 00:42:22,319
if you ever wanted to
search for your parents.

606
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:24,646
But now that you've found your parents

607
00:42:24,670 --> 00:42:27,310
there's no reason for me to
hang onto this anymore.

608
00:42:28,450 --> 00:42:31,760
I think this may have been in the bag
that you were carrying with you.

609
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:40,000
<i>[I know that the
heavens will punish me</i>

610
00:42:40,010 --> 00:42:41,650
<i>[for abandoning my child
at this place...]</i>

611
00:42:42,460 --> 00:42:44,460
<i>[But it's just too
difficult to raise</i>

612
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:46,480
<i>[this child on my own
without his father.]</i>

613
00:42:56,910 --> 00:42:58,939
Have you known about it too?

614
00:42:58,940 --> 00:43:00,280
Excuse me?

615
00:43:01,090 --> 00:43:02,789
I'm sure you were just doing
what you were told.

616
00:43:02,790 --> 00:43:05,760
I have an urgent matter to tend to,
so I'll see you later.

617
00:43:12,120 --> 00:43:14,089
What is this about?

618
00:43:14,090 --> 00:43:16,020
If you could just tell me
what this is about...

619
00:43:39,890 --> 00:43:40,979
Oh my goodness!

620
00:43:40,980 --> 00:43:43,249
- What are you doing here?
- Where's mother's room?

621
00:43:43,250 --> 00:43:45,480
- Mom isn't here right now.
- Is it over there?

622
00:44:22,300 --> 00:44:26,460
Hey... you! You seem to be
mistaken about something here.

623
00:44:26,970 --> 00:44:29,519
But we don't think
of you as family yet.

624
00:44:29,520 --> 00:44:32,299
No, you'll never be our family.
Do you know why?

625
00:44:32,300 --> 00:44:34,120
It's because you're trash.

626
00:44:36,990 --> 00:44:38,529
Take a good look.

627
00:44:38,530 --> 00:44:40,859
Do you actually think that you and I
look like siblings?

628
00:44:40,860 --> 00:44:43,190
No.
Not even close.

629
00:44:44,250 --> 00:44:45,780
Right?

630
00:44:46,590 --> 00:44:48,500
You don't think so either.

631
00:44:57,420 --> 00:44:59,290
What the hell is his deal?

632
00:45:02,540 --> 00:45:04,780
- Straighten that out.
- Yes, Sir.

633
00:45:07,060 --> 00:45:08,740
Yes, Lady Jin Ah.

634
00:45:15,770 --> 00:45:17,650
<i>The caller you are trying
cannot be reached,</i>

635
00:45:17,660 --> 00:45:19,550
<i>so please leave a
message at the tone.</i>

636
00:45:29,450 --> 00:45:31,160
- Yes, Director.
- What happened?

637
00:45:31,170 --> 00:45:33,890
Why did Kang Ji Hyuk suddenly
cause a scene over at the house?

638
00:45:35,350 --> 00:45:38,160
By any chance...
did he catch on to what's going on?

639
00:45:39,540 --> 00:45:42,760
I think Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk discovered
something at the orphanage.

640
00:45:43,310 --> 00:45:44,710
Really?

641
00:45:46,210 --> 00:45:48,689
Do you remember the thing that I told
you to prepare in case of an emergency?

642
00:45:48,690 --> 00:45:50,279
We need to get it ready in a hurry.

643
00:45:50,280 --> 00:45:52,729
Send out a team over to the company.

644
00:45:52,730 --> 00:45:53,890
Okay.

645
00:46:51,260 --> 00:46:53,890
Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk.
What brings you by here?

646
00:46:54,450 --> 00:46:56,699
Where's Chairman Kang right now?

647
00:46:56,700 --> 00:46:59,729
I'm actually trying to locate
where Chairman Kang is myself.

648
00:46:59,730 --> 00:47:01,300
I think he may be away
on a business trip.

649
00:47:01,320 --> 00:47:02,899
Can you get in touch with him?

650
00:47:02,900 --> 00:47:04,449
I'm not sure.

651
00:47:04,450 --> 00:47:05,609
I tried to reach him,
but I wasn't able to get a hold of him.

652
00:47:05,610 --> 00:47:08,980
He may be in the middle of
an important meeting right now.

653
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:11,599
What is it that you
need to see him about?

654
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:14,829
There's something
that I need to verify with him.

655
00:47:14,830 --> 00:47:15,929
Why don't you tell me what it is?

656
00:47:15,930 --> 00:47:18,650
- I can check for you when I see him...
- No.

657
00:47:20,380 --> 00:47:22,760
I'd like to speak to him
directly in person.

658
00:47:23,650 --> 00:47:25,200
I'll just wait for him.

659
00:47:33,740 --> 00:47:35,209
Is there something...

660
00:47:35,210 --> 00:47:37,830
that you're disappointed
with the Chairman about?

661
00:47:38,880 --> 00:47:40,770
It's been quite a
while since I started

662
00:47:40,780 --> 00:47:42,690
working for Chairman
Kang and his family.

663
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:45,210
There's something
that I've learned in

664
00:47:45,230 --> 00:47:46,790
all the years that
I've worked for them.

665
00:47:47,580 --> 00:47:50,720
All the members of that family...
are weary of other people.

666
00:47:50,730 --> 00:47:53,319
Just think about what it would be like
if you had just walked out of a bank

667
00:47:53,320 --> 00:47:55,190
with a huge bag of cash on you.

668
00:47:55,600 --> 00:47:58,350
You begin to be suspicious of everyone
who walks by you.

669
00:47:59,410 --> 00:48:04,310
Same goes for blood ties. No, blood
ties are even more suspicious.

670
00:48:04,830 --> 00:48:06,339
Because closer a person is to you

671
00:48:06,340 --> 00:48:08,621
higher the danger of that person
stabbing you in the back.

672
00:48:12,060 --> 00:48:13,959
You cannot expect...

673
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:16,849
a normal family life
with people like that.

674
00:48:16,850 --> 00:48:18,350
Is that right?

675
00:48:19,700 --> 00:48:22,150
Then... why would people
like that falsely

676
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:24,620
forge up a family
registry document?

677
00:48:26,530 --> 00:48:28,770
I have no idea what it is
that you're implying right now.

678
00:48:31,220 --> 00:48:33,020
Looking at you right now...

679
00:48:33,970 --> 00:48:36,740
I get the feeling that you know this
family better than anyone else.

680
00:48:37,670 --> 00:48:39,550
Then I guess you must
know about it too.

681
00:48:40,870 --> 00:48:42,630
What their true intentions are.

682
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:46,320
Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk.

683
00:48:46,790 --> 00:48:48,910
You seem to be misunderstood
about something.

684
00:48:49,540 --> 00:48:52,360
But you really are
the biological son of Chairman Kang.

685
00:49:01,770 --> 00:49:04,880
There is only one reason why
anyone would show any kindness...

686
00:49:06,810 --> 00:49:08,320
to a stray dog out on the streets.

687
00:49:13,820 --> 00:49:15,910
It's so that they can devour the dog.

688
00:49:19,630 --> 00:49:21,040
Then what do you think
the stray dog in

689
00:49:21,050 --> 00:49:22,730
that situation must do
in order to survive?

690
00:49:24,620 --> 00:49:27,700
The dog must rip them to shreds
as they try to attack.

691
00:49:31,870 --> 00:49:33,550
That's the only way for
the dog to survive!

692
00:49:35,680 --> 00:49:38,319
- What is it that you want from me?
- This is all a misunderstanding.

693
00:49:38,320 --> 00:49:41,320
Do you know what kind of people
I hate the most in this world?

694
00:49:41,680 --> 00:49:44,610
It's those who deceives
me about my parents!

695
00:49:50,910 --> 00:49:54,890
No, that's not true.
You must believe me.

696
00:49:56,390 --> 00:49:58,610
It seems as though
whatever you're hiding is

697
00:49:58,620 --> 00:50:00,860
more important to you
than your own life.

698
00:50:01,550 --> 00:50:03,969
Warn Chairman Kang for me.

699
00:50:03,970 --> 00:50:06,660
Because I'm going to meet him
to get the truth out of him myself.

700
00:50:09,520 --> 00:50:13,730
I'm not that generous of a person... so
you won't' get away easy the next time.

701
00:50:16,960 --> 00:50:18,110
He's...

702
00:50:19,220 --> 00:50:23,130
at the company's 48th
anniversary event right now.

703
00:50:48,850 --> 00:50:50,590
Is Chairman Kang
in there right now?

704
00:50:50,600 --> 00:50:52,340
No, he's not. But
Director Do is in there.

705
00:50:54,670 --> 00:50:56,469
<i>He's on his way there right now.</i>

706
00:50:56,470 --> 00:50:58,930
We don't need to explain
anything to him this time.

707
00:50:59,400 --> 00:51:03,140
Just make it clean...
and get rid of him once and for all.

708
00:51:23,400 --> 00:51:24,900
Don't go.

709
00:51:48,850 --> 00:51:50,559
Please don't go.

710
00:51:50,560 --> 00:51:52,609
I need to go and verify it for myself.

711
00:51:52,610 --> 00:51:54,520
I need to find out who I really am.

712
00:51:54,840 --> 00:51:57,430
Just who it is that I really am.

713
00:52:28,190 --> 00:52:29,590
Hold on.

714
00:52:46,830 --> 00:52:48,460
Yes, I understand.

715
00:53:01,480 --> 00:53:03,050
Move!
Move out of the way!

716
00:53:44,120 --> 00:53:46,310
- Dad.
- You're here.

717
00:53:50,290 --> 00:53:51,849
What is it that you're
wearing right now?

718
00:53:51,850 --> 00:53:54,950
That guy came by the house earlier
and caused a huge ruckus.

719
00:53:55,320 --> 00:53:58,670
- Who did?
- Who do you think? Your firstborn son.

720
00:53:59,330 --> 00:54:01,150
Let's talk about that later.

721
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:05,010
He's fake, isn't he?

722
00:54:06,510 --> 00:54:09,640
- Chairman Cha... you came.
- Yes.

723
00:54:13,880 --> 00:54:16,560
It's me.
We can't let that bastard go in there.

724
00:54:16,870 --> 00:54:19,490
Stop him. Stop him even if
you have to ram him down.

725
00:56:03,800 --> 00:56:05,280
What are you planning
to do in there?

726
00:56:05,290 --> 00:56:06,890
I don't know what I'm
going to do either.

727
00:56:08,210 --> 00:56:09,650
I believe that the
only reason Hyun Sung

728
00:56:09,660 --> 00:56:11,099
has been able to endure
the past 48 years

729
00:56:11,100 --> 00:56:13,540
was because of the efforts
put in by everyone at the company.

730
00:56:21,050 --> 00:56:23,819
A leader with the correct set of
principles and experience...

731
00:56:23,820 --> 00:56:25,400
and all the family
members at Hyun Sung who

732
00:56:25,410 --> 00:56:26,990
followed that leadership
with loyalty.

733
00:56:32,050 --> 00:56:33,729
I will do everything within my power

734
00:56:33,730 --> 00:56:35,830
to grow the strength
further to last another

735
00:56:35,840 --> 00:56:37,960
48 years, and longer
into the future.

736
00:56:39,050 --> 00:56:41,309
My Hyun Sung family...

737
00:56:41,310 --> 00:56:43,470
and everyone else who has
dedicated themselves

738
